Hermès International S.A., Hermès of Paris, or simply Hermès (French pronunciation: ​[ɛʁmɛs];  ( listen)) is a French high fashion luxury goods manufacturer established in 1837. It specializes in leather, lifestyle accessories, home furnishings, perfumery, jewellery, watches and ready-to-wear. Its logo, since the 1950s, is of a Duc carriage with horse. Nadège Vanhee-Cybulski is the current creative director.
